Document: OpenXRSpatialAnchorCapability
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrspatialanchorcapability.rst
Summary: Defines the capabilities of OpenXR spatial anchor services.

Inherits: Object < Object

This class defines the capabilities of OpenXR spatial anchor services. It is used to query whether specific spatial anchor features are supported by the OpenXR runtime.

Properties:
anchor_supported (bool): Whether the OpenXR runtime supports creating and managing spatial anchors. Default: false.
cloud_anchor_supported (bool): Whether the OpenXR runtime supports cloud anchors, which allow anchors to be shared across devices and sessions. Default: false.
persistence_supported (bool): Whether the OpenXR runtime supports persistent anchors, which survive application restarts. Default: false.
room_scale_anchor_supported (bool): Whether the OpenXR runtime supports anchors tied to the room's scale. Default: false.
space_preserving_anchor_supported (bool): Whether the OpenXR runtime supports anchors that preserve space, meaning they remain fixed in the real world even if the user moves. Default: false.
